# 1. Why VictoriaMetrics for LLM Workloads

## 1.1 The specific challenge of LLM metrics

LLM workloads in production generate an atypical metrics profile that pushes classic monitoring backends to their limits:

| **LLM Characteristic** | **Impact on the metrics backend**                                                                |
|------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| High cardinality       | model \* provider \* tenant \* pipeline = thousands of timeseries. Prometheus saturates quickly. |
| Token histograms       | Wide distributions (10 to 100k tokens/request). Very spread-out buckets.                         |
| USD cost metrics       | Financial metrics requiring float precision. Aggregations by accounting period.                  |
| Long retention         | Cost audits, contractual SLAs: 1-3 year retention is often required.                             |
| Ingestion bursts       | A completion batch can generate 10x the normal write rate in seconds.                            |
| RAG quality metrics    | Floats, distributions, scores: write-intensive, frequently read for alerting.                    |

## 1.2 VictoriaMetrics vs Prometheus - head-to-head

| **Criteria**     | **Prometheus**                    | **VictoriaMetrics**                                      |
|------------------|-----------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| Cardinality      | Degrades above 500k active series | Stable up to 10M+ active series                          |
| Compression      | ~4:1 ratio                        | ~10:1 ratio (20:1 with long retention)                   |
| Write throughput | ~200k samples/s per instance      | \>1M samples/s on a standard instance                    |
| Long retention   | Degrades after 90 days            | Performant over 2+ years without manual compaction       |
| Query language   | PromQL                            | MetricsQL (superset: anomaly_score, median_over_time...) |
| Native OTLP      | Via Collector only                | Direct OTLP endpoint in Single mode (port 4318)          |
| Deployment       | Multiple recommended components   | Single binary in Single mode                             |
| RAM footprint    | 4 GB RAM / 500k series            | 1 GB RAM / 500k series (4x less)                         |
| Migration        | N/A                               | 100% Prometheus-compatible API: zero dashboard migration |

