# 5. LLM Metrics Taxonomy

The taxonomy below covers the four dimensions of LLM observability: response quality, performance and latency, costs and tokens, and GPU/CPU infrastructure.

![](./media/image3.png)

*Diagram 3 : Complete LLM metrics taxonomy for VictoriaMetrics - 4 dimensions, recommended labels, alert thresholds*

## 5.1 Recommended naming conventions

- Prefix llm\_ for all LLM-specific metrics

- Prefix rag\_ for retrieval-specific metrics

- Use DCGM standard names for GPU metrics (DCGM_FI\_\*)

- Standard suffixes: \_total (counter), \_seconds/\_ms (latency histogram), \_ratio (0-1 gauge), \_bytes (gauge)

| **Metric**                 | **Prometheus Type** | **Cardinality** | **Essential Labels**                     |
|----------------------------|---------------------|-----------------|------------------------------------------|
| llm_request_duration_ms    | Histogram           | Medium          | model, provider, pipeline_id, status     |
| llm_tokens_total{type}     | Counter             | Low             | model, provider, type=input\|output      |
| llm_cost_usd_total         | Counter             | Low             | model, provider, tenant_id, use_case     |
| llm_errors_total           | Counter             | Medium          | model, provider, error_type, status_code |
| llm_ttft_ms                | Histogram           | Medium          | model, provider, stream=true\|false      |
| rag_retrieval_score_avg    | Gauge               | Low             | index_id, pipeline_id, strategy          |
| rag_context_pressure_ratio | Histogram           | Low             | pipeline_id, model, tenant_id            |
| rag_chunks_dropped_total   | Counter             | Low             | pipeline_id, reason                      |
| DCGM_FI_DEV_GPU_UTIL       | Gauge               | Low             | gpu, UUID, pod, namespace, node          |
| vllm:num_requests_running  | Gauge               | Low             | model_name, instance                     |

> **Cardinality warning: tenant_id label**
>
> If you have more than 1000 tenants, the tenant_id label can cause a cardinality explosion.
>
> Solution: use a tenant_tier label (free/pro/enterprise) for high-frequency metrics,
>
> and keep tenant_id only for cost metrics (llm_cost_usd_total) which have low write frequency.

