# 11. Optimization, Retention and Tuning

## 11.1 Retention policy by metric type

| **Metric type**        | **Recommended retention** | **Justification**                  | **VM flag**           |
|------------------------|---------------------------|------------------------------------|-----------------------|
| USD cost metrics       | 2-3 years                 | Accounting audit, contractual SLAs | --retentionPeriod=24m |
| RAG quality scores     | 6-12 months               | Long-term drift detection          | --retentionPeriod=12m |
| Latency and throughput | 3-6 months                | Performance trending               | --retentionPeriod=6m  |
| GPU metrics            | 1-3 months                | Capacity planning                  | --retentionPeriod=3m  |
| OTel traces (Jaeger)   | 7-30 days                 | Debug, no long-term audit          | Jaeger TTL config     |

## 11.2 Cardinality optimisation

- Never label by trace_id, request_id or session_id - infinite cardinality.

- Restrict tenant_id to cost metrics only (not for latency or token metrics).

- Group similar models under a model_family label if more than 20 active versions.

- Use adapted histogram buckets for tokens: \[10, 100, 500, 1000, 4096, 16384, 65536\].

