# 12. Security, Air-Gap and Compliance

## 12.1 Authentication and access control

- VictoriaMetrics has no native authentication. Use vmauth (open-source) or an Nginx reverse proxy.

- vmauth supports role-based routing: read-only for Grafana, write-only for OTel Collector, admin for ops.

- Kubernetes NetworkPolicy: restrict access to VM ports to authorised components only.

| \# vmauth config                                    |
|-----------------------------------------------------|
| users:                                              |
| \- username: grafana                                |
| password: '\${GRAFANA_PASSWORD}'                    |
| url_prefix:                                         |
| \- 'http://victoriametrics:8428/api/v1/query'       |
| \- 'http://victoriametrics:8428/api/v1/query_range' |
|                                                     |
| \- username: otel-collector                         |
| password: '\${OTEL_PASSWORD}'                       |
| url_prefix:                                         |
| \- 'http://victoriametrics:8428/api/v1/write'       |

## 12.2 Compliance checklist for LLM metrics

| **Compliance point**   | **Recommended implementation**                                     |
|------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
| PII in metrics         | Never label with user query content. Use opaque IDs only.          |
| Cost audit (GDPR/NIS2) | 3-year retention on llm_cost_usd_total. Monthly CSV export.        |
| Encryption in transit  | TLS on all VM endpoints in production (vmauth or reverse proxy).   |
| Multi-tenant isolation | vmauth for per-tenant access segmentation. Grafana Teams + RBAC.   |
| Backup                 | vmbackup incremental to S3-compatible storage (MinIO for air-gap). |
| Dashboard access       | Grafana with SSO (LDAP, OIDC). Viewer-only for business teams.     |

