# 18. FAQ and troubleshooting

**Q1. VMAlert does not fire even with an obvious metric.**

Check 3 things: (1) is the rule actually loaded? GET http://vmalert:8880/-/reload then http://vmalert:8880/api/v1/rules. (2) does the query return any series? Test in vmui. (3) is the 'for:' attribute too long? An alert with for: 30m waits 30 minutes.

**Q2. Cardinality explodes after adding a new service.**

Run GET http://victoriametrics:8428/api/v1/status/tsdb to identify top labels. Often a trace_id or request_id label has leaked. Quick fix: vmagent --remoteWrite.relabelConfig to drop the label.

**Q3. My recording rules do not update.**

VMAlert reloads rules every 60 seconds by default. Force reload: curl -X POST http://vmalert:8880/-/reload. Check logs for 'failed to load rule'.

**Q4. Difference between vmagent and vmauth?**

vmagent = scraping and remote_write client (Prometheus equivalent on the collection side). vmauth = reverse proxy with authentication and per-tenant routing (useful for multi-tenant and air-gap).

**Q5. How do I know when to switch to Cluster mode?**

Three signals: RAM used \> 70% of host, P99 query \> 3 seconds, disk filling up despite compression. Beyond that, plan a Cluster migration over 2 weeks.

**Q6. My Prometheus histograms compute P99 incorrectly.**

Check the buckets: if the real P99 exceeds the last finite bucket, the result is +Inf or clamped. For LLMs, plan buckets up to 30 seconds: \[.05, .1, .25, .5, 1, 2.5, 5, 10, 30\].

**Q7. I lose points in remote_write from Prometheus.**

Tune queue_config in prometheus.yml: capacity, max_shards, max_samples_per_send. Watch prometheus_remote_storage_samples_dropped_total. If non-zero, raise max_shards.

**Q8. How do I export my data to a 3rd-party platform (DataDog, New Relic)?**

VictoriaMetrics exposes /api/v1/export in JSON. For continuous exports, use vmagent with two remote_write: one to VM, one to the 3rd party. Watch out for cost: each sample is double-billed.

**Q9. My Unicode labels (Chinese, accents) break queries.**

VictoriaMetrics supports UTF-8 but Grafana may render poorly. Wrap values in back-ticks and prefer ASCII labels for business values (e.g., tenant_id as slug).

**Q10. My dashboard loads in 10 seconds after adding a variable.**

A Grafana variable = a sub-query on every refresh. Solutions: (1) cache the variable in Grafana (refresh on dashboard load), (2) pre-aggregate via recording rule, (3) limit options with sort + limit.

**Q11. A GPU disappears from DCGM exporter metrics.**

DCGM exporter uses NVML which can lose the GPU list if the driver crashes. Check nvidia-smi on the node, restart dcgm-exporter and nvidia-persistenced. For prevention: alert on absent(DCGM_FI_DEV_GPU_UTIL{node='X'}).

**Q12. How do I version my VMAlert alerts?**

Store YAML files in Git, use ArgoCD or Flux for deployment, vmalert reads files from a volume. Test each PR with promtool check rules.

**Q13. Difference between rate() and increase() for costs?**

rate(llm_cost_usd_total\[5m\]) returns USD per second. increase(llm_cost_usd_total\[1h\]) returns the total delta over 1h in USD. For displayed hourly cost, prefer increase. For projection, prefer rate.

**Q14. My alerts send duplicates to Slack.**

Check Alertmanager configuration: group_by, group_wait, group_interval. For LLMs, group_by: \['alertname', 'model'\] groups alerts per model, repeat_interval: 4h prevents spam.

**Q15. Point-in-time backup: which strategy?**

vmbackup to S3-compatible (MinIO in air-gap). Daily incremental snapshots, 30-day retention. Mandatory monthly restore test. Typical storage cost: 5% of live data.

**APPENDIX A**

# Appendix A. Glossary

**Anomaly score:** MetricsQL function that measures how far a series deviates from a historical baseline. Value \> 1 = anomaly.

**Burn rate:** Speed at which the error budget is consumed. Burn rate = 1 = linear consumption over the SLO window.

**Cardinality:** Number of unique time series (metric + label combinations).

**Chunk:** Document fragment indexed in a vector database for RAG.

**Context pressure:** Ratio of used tokens to the model's context window. \> 0.85 = truncation risk.

**Counter:** Metric type that only increases (except on reset). Ex: total requests.

**DCGM:** NVIDIA Data Center GPU Manager. Source of real-time GPU metrics.

**Embedding:** Vector representation of text computed by an embedding model.

**Error budget:** Tolerated error margin allowed by the SLO over a given window.

**Fan-out:** Cardinality multiplier resulting from label combinations.

**Gauge:** Metric type that can go up and down. Ex: GPU utilization.

**Hallucination rate:** Estimated rate of non-factual responses, measured by evaluators or heuristics.

**Histogram:** Metric type that distributes values into buckets to compute quantiles.

**Index drift:** Drift in retrieval score after reindexing, sign of an embedding or corpus change.

**KV cache:** Cache of attention keys/values in a Transformer model during inference.

**Latency P99:** 99th percentile of latency: 99% of requests are faster.

**LiteLLM:** Unified proxy that exposes OpenAI, Anthropic, Mistral etc. APIs behind a common interface.

**MetricsQL:** VictoriaMetrics query language, superset of PromQL.

**OpenTelemetry (OTel):** Instrumentation standard for traces, metrics and logs.

**OTLP:** OpenTelemetry Protocol: binary (gRPC) or JSON (HTTP) format for exporting telemetry.

**Prompt template:** Prompt skeleton with variables, versioned like code.

**RAG:** Retrieval Augmented Generation: enriching a prompt with retrieved documents.

**Recording rule:** Rule that pre-computes a derived metric and stores it as a new series.

**Remote write:** Protocol for pushing metrics from a Prometheus/vmagent to a remote TSDB.

**Retrieval score:** Similarity score (0 to 1) between a question and the chunks returned by RAG.

**Single mode (VM):** VictoriaMetrics deployment as a single binary, up to 1M active series.

**Cluster mode (VM):** VictoriaMetrics deployment in 3 components (vminsert, vmstorage, vmselect) for horizontal scale.

**SLI:** Service Level Indicator: the metric being measured.

**SLO:** Service Level Objective: internal target on the SLI.

**SLA:** Service Level Agreement: contractual commitment with an external customer.

**Tenant:** Logical customer of a multi-tenant platform, isolated by tenant_id.

**Token:** Text-splitting unit for an LLM (sub-word), billed by providers.

**TSDB:** Time Series Database. VictoriaMetrics, Prometheus, InfluxDB are TSDBs.

**TTFT:** Time To First Token: latency before the first token of a streamed response.

**vLLM:** High-performance open-source inference engine for LLMs.

**VMAgent:** VictoriaMetrics component that scrapes and does remote_write.

**VMAlert:** VictoriaMetrics component that evaluates alerting and recording rules.

**VMAuth:** VictoriaMetrics reverse proxy with authentication and per-tenant routing.

**VMSelect:** VictoriaMetrics Cluster component that serves queries.

**VMStorage:** VictoriaMetrics Cluster component that stores data.

**VMUI:** VictoriaMetrics built-in web UI (vmui).

**VRAM:** Video memory of a GPU (HBM, GDDR). Limits the loadable model size.

**APPENDIX B**

# Appendix B. MetricsQL cheat sheet for LLMs

## Cost and tokens

> # Hourly cost per model
>
> sum by(model) (increase(llm_cost_usd_total[1h]))
>
> # Projected daily cost
>
> sum(rate(llm_cost_usd_total[30m])) * 86400
>
> # Top 10 tenants over 24h
>
> topk(10, sum by(tenant_id) (increase(llm_cost_usd_total[24h])))
>
> # Average cost per request (recording rule recommended)
>
> sum(rate(llm_cost_usd_total[5m])) / sum(rate(llm_requests_total[5m]))

## Latency and performance

> # P99 end-to-end latency per model
>
> histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by(le, model) (rate(llm_request_duration_ms_bucket[5m])))
>
> # TTFT P95 (streaming)
>
> histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by(le, model) (rate(llm_ttft_ms_bucket[5m])))
>
> # Global error rate
>
> sum(rate(llm_errors_total[5m])) / sum(rate(llm_requests_total[5m]))
>
> # Throughput tokens/s per model
>
> sum by(model) (rate(llm_tokens_total{type='output'}[1m]))

## RAG quality

> # Retrieval score anomaly (7-day baseline)
>
> anomaly_score(avg by(index_id) (rag_retrieval_score_avg), "7d")
>
> # P95 context pressure per pipeline
>
> histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by(le, pipeline_id) (rate(rag_context_pressure_ratio_bucket[5m])))
>
> # Dropped chunks rate (information loss)
>
> sum by(pipeline_id) (rate(rag_chunks_dropped_total[5m]))
>
> / sum by(pipeline_id) (rate(rag_chunks_retrieved_total[5m]))

## GPU and infrastructure

> # Average GPU utilization per node
>
> avg by(node, gpu) (DCGM_FI_DEV_GPU_UTIL)
>
> # VRAM saturation (alert before OOM)
>
> DCGM_FI_DEV_FB_USED / DCGM_FI_DEV_FB_TOTAL
>
> # Tokens per watt (efficiency)
>
> sum by(model) (rate(llm_tokens_total{type='output'}[5m]))
>
> / sum by(model) (avg(DCGM_FI_DEV_POWER_USAGE))
>
> # vLLM queue
>
> vllm:num_requests_waiting

## Advanced patterns

> # Robust median (ignores spikes)
>
> median_over_time(llm_tokens_per_request_avg[30m])
>
> # OHLC on RAG scores (candlestick visualization)
>
> rollup_candlestick(rag_retrieval_score_avg[1h])
>
> # Plateau detection (rate of change < 1%)
>
> abs(deriv(llm_requests_total[10m])) < 0.01
>
> # Week-over-week comparison
>
> sum(rate(llm_cost_usd_total[1h]))
>
> / sum(rate(llm_cost_usd_total[1h] offset 7d))

**APPENDIX C**

# Appendix C. Production go-live checklist

## Before go-live

• \[ \] VictoriaMetrics is deployed with --storageDataPath on a persistent SSD disk

• \[ \] Retention flags are set (--retentionPeriod and --retentionFilter)

• \[ \] vmbackup is configured to S3-compatible storage (restore test passed)

• \[ \] vmagent or OTel Collector ingests the 4 metric categories (quality, latency, cost, GPU)

• \[ \] The 6 production VMAlert rules are loaded and tested (test alert received in Slack/Teams)

• \[ \] At least 2 recording rules are active for costs (Grafana performance gain)

• \[ \] The production Grafana dashboard is imported, template variables work

• \[ \] vmauth is configured with basic auth or mTLS (never unauthenticated access)

• \[ \] Total cardinality is measured and documented (curl /api/v1/status/tsdb)

• \[ \] Risky labels (trace_id, session_id) are dropped via relabelConfig

• \[ \] The 'VictoriaMetricsDown' (self-monitoring) alert is active

• \[ \] An incident runbook exists (who to call, how to restore, how to scale)

• \[ \] Read-only Grafana users are created for non-tech roles (management, finance)

## After go-live (D+7, D+30)

• \[ \] Verify cardinality has stabilized (no linear growth)

• \[ \] Verify disk consumption and project to 90 days

• \[ \] Receive at least one real alert and confirm routing works

• \[ \] Measure P99 latency of Grafana queries (\< 1s expected)

• \[ \] Run a vmbackup restore test on a test instance

• \[ \] Review alert thresholds with teams (false positives?)

• \[ \] Document custom MetricsQL queries used by teams
